                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/1817</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Santo Domingo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-05-05T12:00:00-04:40">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 5, 1916, noon</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>President with all his forces advanced on the city and demanded surrender of
                    fort. Fighting commenced and <hi rend="italic">Prairie</hi> has landed force for
                    the protection of Legation. Foreigners are massed in Haitian Legation under the
                    protection of guard from <hi rend="italic">Castine.</hi>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Russell</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
